rComments: Learned his history in the 1960s and 1970s and stuck with the mentality. Interesting prof but will not acknowledge other perspectives. Fairly easy marker though, as far as seminars go. He does love to lecture and for a seminar this was difficult. Tons of reading, sometimes assigning 15 chapters in a week.

He was average, not the best professor I've had but definately not the worse.  His lectures need to be more ogranized and he needs to put all the due dates on the syllabus instead of giving them as he explains assignments.

VERY intelligent,knowledgeable and nice prof. He has achieved the status of a fellow of the Royal Society of Canada which is huge. He does a lot of work for newspapers & such. Worked with many great Canadian historians. AMAZING Prof & man! As long as you do the  work, you will get the mark. The term paper is long but normal for history students!
Really boring teacher!! Be prepared to write an 18 page paper. Almost never present during his office hours so meet with his TA. He was extremely rude to me because I was sick.

I can see how a seminar with Professor Behiels would be really interesting and I think he's a really decent and respectful man with a good heart. I didn't enjoy his class, however. All of the lectures focussed on the political aspects of Canadian history and nothing else. Be prepared to write an 18 page paper!!!

AWFUL professor. He has way too much information on his powerpoints, refuses to see you outside of office hours if you can't make them, very arrogant, and not an interesting lecturer. Knows his stuff well, but does not teach it well. His papers are scary, but you will learn to write. Textbooks barely used. If only he was good.

Ha is the most useless teacher I've ever had. He doesn't care if you succeed or not. He refuses to answer any questions by e-mail and he refused to see anyone outside his office hours( for those of us who have other classes or work). The class load is really heavy (which I didn't mind at fist) but now I do..
canadian history is boring and he doesn't do much to liven it up. see adam greene to know how its done. contemporary can. hist. shouldnt end in 1939!!!!!
Very poor teacher.  More interested in driving home a socialist message than teaching history.  Poor listener.  Very unclear on expectations of students.  More stuck in history than a student of it.

Awesome prof! He is a role model for me! An absolute expert on Canadian political history, fair marker with very clear assignments and very helpful. A Canadian patriot, but he respects different opinions.

Knows his stuff and explains it really well, but be prepared to frantically copy down his overheads which are WAY too detailed and sometimes don't make sense.  Also, his TA will grade EVERYTHING except the final exam.  He won't even look over the assignments.  Mainly, ask questions.  It's easy, but copying down the overheads can be really tedious.
Unbelievably arrogant. Hard to approach. Not as effective as he could be given his arrogance. Chill out a bit, friend.
Excellent prof! Course is well organized- lectures interesting. Term paper is a bit overwelming- but he does not require much other course work (6 short article summaries & 1 presentation)
A good professor. He doesnt use notes, yet is very organized and clear-he knows his stuff. He asks for a 20-page term paper, but is fair in marking.
Term paper...frightening length. However, great lectures, never boring, and it's great to be taught a history course by a true expert in the field.
firm but fair. is hard one you but rewards you for for good work
Puts a great deal of information in the course... knows what he is talking about... longest 2nd year term paper I've ever written

Such a friendly man!! Very intimidating at first, but he's really not. Expects a lot in the term paper, but the topics he gives are all appropriate to the length he expects. Overheads are helpful, but it can get a little boring at times. Overall, good.
Easily one of the most ARROGANT men I have ever met.Belittles some students
ever been spoon fed before? it's boring
He demands a lot from students, especially for the term paper.
I like his lecturing, but i've not done the paper yet.
No room for opinions that differ from his own!
Teaches well....the only thing you have to worry about is the term paper!
